Unfortunately, my search for a good nearby Jamaican restaurant continues.

They need to change the name to Last Resort Jamaican  Restaurant.  When they first opened the food was fresh, tasty and delicious.  They have been open for a couple of months and the food and the customer service is very negative.  First off  the people who work the front counter are very lazy and rude.  The food is below average but the prices are high.  Every time I go there they never have available the food on the menu.  It is a shame that in order to get a beef patty and coco bread I can find it at the Italian Pizza store across the street, but Top choice very rarely sells it.  Also this is a brand new restaurant and they received a B rating from Health Department.  They need to close this place.

Excellent!!!! From CT, happened to be in the area and craving Jamaican food. Absolutely amazing and the ladies give great portion sizes. I got the curried goat and a fried dumpling. Some of the best goat I've had in awhile!!! ❤ Will def be back!

Went on a cruise to the Caribbean and one port of call was Jamaica. Got introduced to the islands cuisine and  really enjoyed it. Returned home and have been missing that island taste until I came across TOP CHOICE Jamaican and West Indian restaurant at 746 Lydig Ave, Bronx, NY 10462. This is the flavor of the dishes I remembered, real authentic. There are only four tables for dining so this is mainly an order and go place, I don’t mind that as I really like to “dig in” to their food and that might become embarrassing. I am always greeted with a smile by the staff and everything I have tried on the menu has been excellent (plan on making my way through entire menu). If ever in this part of town and wanting a savory meal I recommend you give this place a visit.

Here we are in Lydig neighborhood! A well deserved addition to the list of restaurants on Lydig Ave. & White Plains Rd., Bronx NY 10462 making our neighborhood skyrocket to the top 5 neighborhoods for great food in Da Bx The amazing "Choice Jamacian Restaurant" opens 6:00am to 2:00 am! Kennedy's Fried Chicken, was the only restaurant that was open pass midnight but now the neighborhood is blessed with Top Choice Jamacian Restaurant where we can finally catch something hot and delicious to eat when ppl in da hood get home from work at midnight. Thank You Top Choice hard working ppl for providing our neighborhood with more choices of great food 🥘 👍🏼👍🏼😊
